cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CC, cs.NA. 

The paper presents an algorithm for maintaining maximal matching in a graph under addition and deletion of edges, which is a problem related to graph theory and algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of the expected amortized time for each edge update, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper mentions a two approximate vertex cover maintenance scheme, which involves numerical analysis and optimization, indicating that it may also belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
